    "Even the Warburg scholar <a href=\"/saxlf\">Fritz Saxl</a>, who admitted in a 1934 letter that Wittkower's ideas on the history of art were much different from his own, concluded that Wittkower's \"struggle for clear-shaped logical notions in art history has undoubted merits.\"": [],
